    "But harmful content generated at scale, or by polarized groups, could easily spread in these private channels outside the DSA's scope [78].",
    "Thus, a solely liability-driven approach might underestimate collective social responsibilities around ethical speech cultivation.Allocating Moderation Resources Under a geopolitical lens, a possible unintended impact for moderation activities is the \"Brussels effect\" whereby resources are disproportionately allocated to mitigating EU-specific risks-likely identified in assessments (Code: RA) or gauged by EU public opinion-negatively affecting content moderation practices elsewhere globally.",
    "This underscores needs for research into differential impacts of the DSA's provisions across regions [78,169].Lack of Direct Journalist Protections The DSA introduces key provisions aimed at improving online safety also for the Media and Journalism sector.",
    "These provisions (Code: NTD, DD) empower trusted flaggers to identify and address illegal content (Article 22), allow national authorities to issue orders for the removal of harmful content (Article 9), and establish effective mechanisms for content notification and action (Article 16).",
    "The risk governance system as laid down in Articles 34, 35 and 37 could play a part in the protection of journalistic and news media content."
